Text.Value: Is this one of Blaze Portyr's infamous punishments?
Are you kidding? This is Blaze Portyr - the leader of the Flaming Fist! She once crushed a man's skull with her bare hand.

EditorData.NodeContext: clearly scared of his leader and the very thought of standing up to her

Text.Value: Thanks.
I can't believe it - they actually executed Counsellor Florrick. I didn't know a person could turn so... purple.
I... stole a purse from the evidence room. It was stupid, and I swore to Blaze Portyr I'd never do it again! Ever.
Leave.
You're a Flaming Fist - how dare you steal from the people you're supposed to protect?!
I have no idea.
I'm sorry, all right! It was the spur of the moment, and I'm sorry.
Yes. I... stole a purse from the evidence room. It was stupid, and I swore to Blaze Portyr I'd never do it again! Ever.
If you were truly sorry, you would be working night and day. You would be willing to die for forgiveness.
Don't distract me! It's all I can do to stay balanced.
I have to stand on one leg until she believes me.
It - it was just a purse, mate. Bloody hells, you make Blaze Portyr look like a softie.

EditorData.NodeContext: shocked at player's outburst, grumbling to himself at last line

Text.Value: Were I your master I would  make you cut off your own hand. Be grateful to this Portyr.
Pretend to push him.
Good luck.
Such blind obedience. Stand up to this Portyr - prove to her that you are not a weakling.
How long is that going to take?

EditorData.stateContext: Left leg on the ground, right leg raised, arms out for balance

Text.Value: Suddenly being made to stand on one foot for hours doesn't seem like such a bad punishment.
A valuable discipline for a guard! Centre yourself on nothingness.
I'll leave you in peace.
Tempus help me, a monk! Could you please take a vow of silence until I'm done here? You know, so I can centre myself.
That's not funny! If I fall, I have to start all over.
Shh. I just have to last... a little longer.
Why are you standing on one leg?
I can't, all right? I just can't.

EditorData.NodeContext: clearly scared of his leader and the very thought of standing up to her

Text.Value: Sweet mercies, thank you.

Synopsis: This Fist is standing guard at the gate that leads to basilisk gate barracks. He is balancing on one leg as punishment for stealing something from the evidence room. His right leg is raised.
